<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 12 at 8:30AM CDT  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>A disturbance in the upper portions of the atmosphere is
interacting with limited moisture to produce isolated showers this
morning. Sufficient energy could allow for one or two
thunderstorms to develop through the morning hours producing brief
moderate to heavy rainfall and possible pea size hail along with
some gusty winds. Through 10 AM showers will be moving quickly to
the northeast around 40 mph through portions of Hidalgo, Cameron,
Willacy and Kenedy Counties. Slick roads and briefly reduced
visibility are likely where the heaviest rainfall may pass over.</description>
